superior a denial of their divine right to command not only do mgr lefebvre not deny the divine right of the pope to command but he affirm repeatedly hi recognition of the pope authority and hi intention of never break away from rome the archbishop make hi attitude clear in the issue of day we pray for the pope every day nothing ha change with the consecration last june we be not sedevacantist we recognize in john paul ius the legitimate pope of the catholic church we do even say that he be a heretical pope we only say that hi modernist action favor heresy intrinsically schismatic the principal argument use by those claim that mgr lefebvre be in schism be that the consecration of a bishop without a papal mandate be an intrinsically schismatic act a bishop who carry out such a consecration it be claim become ipso facto a schismatic thi be not true if such a consecration be an intrinsically schismatic act it would alway have involve the penalty of excommunication in the code of canon law the offence wa punish only by suspension see canon of the code pope piu xius have raise the penalty to excommunication a a response to the establishment of a schismatic church in china the consecration of these illicit chinese bishop differ radically from the consecration carry out by mgr lefebvre a the profess intention wa to repudiate the authority of the pope that be to deny that he ha the right to govern the church and the illicitly consecrate chinese bishop be give a mandate to exercise an apostolic mission neither archbishop lefebvre nor any of the bishop he ha consecrate claim that they have power of jurisdiction they have be consecrate solely for the purpose of ensure the survival of the society by carry out ordination and also to perform confirmation i do not wish to minimize in any way the gravity of the step take by mgr lefebvre the consecration of bishop without a papal mandate be far more seriou matter than the ordination of priest a it involf a refusal in practice of the