out the least shred of sympathy for mgr lefebvre have repudiate the charge of schism make against him a totally untenable father patrick yaldrini dean of the faculty of canon law of the institut catholique in pari note in the july issue of valeur actuelle that a i have just explain mgr lefebvre wa not excommunicate for schism but for the usurpation of an ecclesiastical function he add that it be not the consecration of a bishop which constitute schism but the conferral of an apostolic mission upon the illicitly consecrate bishop it be thi usurpation of the power of the sovereign pontiff which prove the intention of establish a parallel church cardinal rosalio lara president of the pontifical commission for the authentic interpretation of canon law comment on the consecration in the july issue of la repubblica it would be hard to imagine a more authoritative opinion the cardinal write the act of consecrate a bishop without a papal mandate be not in itself a schismatic act in fact the code that deal with offense be divide into two section one deal with offense against religion and the unity of the church and these be apostasy schism and heresy consecrating a bishop with a pontifical mandate be on the contrary an offense against the exercise of a specific ministry for example in the case of the consecration carry out by the vietnamese archbishop ngo dinh thuc in and although the archbishop wa excommunicate he wa not consider to have commit a schismatic act because there wa no intention of a breach with the church it be not simply unjust but ludicrou to suggest that in consecrate bishop without a papal mandate archbishop lefebvre have the least intent of establish a schismatic church he be not a schismatic and will never be a schismatic the archbishop consider correctly that the the church be undergo it worst crisi since the arian heresy and that for the good of the church it wa necessary for him to consecrate the fmy bishop to ensure the future of hi society canon law provide for just such a situation and even if one believe that the future of the society could have be guarantee without these consecration the fact that the archbishop believe sincerely that it could not mean a canon law state clearly that he ha not incur excommunication furthermore while the vatican allow such prelate a archbishop weakland to undermine the faith with impunity it can not expect catholic to pay the least attention to it sanction against a great and orthodox archbishop whose entire life ha be devote to the service of the church and the salvation of soul dr eric m de saventhem president of the international una voce association be one of the best inform layman in the church and he know the archbishop intimately dr de saventhem like myself ha no greater desire than to see a reconciliation between mgr lefebvre and the holy see during the archbishop lifetime a quotation from a statement by dr de saventhem which wa publish in the february remnant merit careful study in retrospect the road lead to the consecration of june appear more pave with grave roman and unfortunately also papal omission than with lefebvrist obstinancy and from the eye of an inform public thi can not be hide by attempt to present the archbishop act of grave disobedience a an offense against the faith it be say today that mgr lefebvre ha an erroneou concept of tradition if thi be so cardinal ratzinger could not on behalf of the pope have address to the archbishop the follow word in hi letter of july ymy ardent desire to safeguard tradition by procure for it mean to live and prosper testify to ymy attachment to the faith of all time the holy father understand ymy concern and share it 